EPICS is a service-learning design program in which teams of students partner with local and global community organizations to address human, community, and environmental needs

Advisor (2020- present)
======
Global Design of Assistive Technology (GDAT)
- Guiding and enabling students to understand and implement a design process.
- Mentoring students towards achieving goals and delivering a product to their community partner in Ireland.
- Assisting students with any technical difficulties they may face in the Engineering design process.
- https://epics-gdat.wixsite.com/gdat 


Teaching Assistant (2017-2019) 
======
- GDAT (https://epics-gdat.wixsite.com/gdat)
- MOBI (https://epics.ecn.purdue.edu/mobi/)
- GAPS (https://epics.ecn.purdue.edu/gaps)
- I2R (https://epics.ecn.purdue.edu/i2r)
- BME (https://epics.ecn.purdue.edu/bme)

Won the esteemed Magoon award for Excellence in Teaching in 2018. This award recognizes outstanding teaching assistants and instructors through funds generated by a trust established by Estes H. and Vashti L. Magoon.
